  <div class="news-item">
    <h2>🔥 Vulnerabilities</h2>

    <p>🧩 <b>CISA Adds SAP NetWeaver CVE-2025-31324 to KEV Catalog</b><br>
    Critical SAP Visual Composer flaw allows unauthenticated RCE. Attackers deployed JSP webshells; patch immediately recommended.<br>
    🔗 <a href="https://www.cisa.gov/news-events/alerts/2025/04/29/cisa-adds-one-known-exploited-vulnerability-catalog" target="_blank">Read more</a></p>

    <p>🍏 <b>Apple AirBorne Flaws Enable Zero-Click AirPlay RCE Attacks</b><br>
    Oligo Security uncovered 23 flaws in AirPlay, including wormable RCE vulnerabilities. Updates issued across iOS, macOS, and visionOS.<br>
    🔗 <a href="https://www.bleepingcomputer.com/news/security/apple-airborne-flaws-can-lead-to-zero-click-airplay-rce-attacks/" target="_blank">Read more</a></p>

    <p>🔍 <b>Google: Over 75 Zero-Days Exploited in 2024</b><br>
    Spyware campaigns drove most zero-day abuse, increasingly targeting enterprise systems like Ivanti and Cisco.<br>
    🔗 <a href="https://www.bleepingcomputer.com/news/security/google-97-zero-days-exploited-in-2024-over-50-percent-in-spyware-attacks/" target="_blank">Read more</a></p>

    <p>⛽ <b>Internet-Connected Fuel Tank Systems Found Vulnerable</b><br>
    Research reveals over 11,000 vulnerable automatic tank gauges (ATGs) exposed online with weak security, posing major risks.<br>
    🔗 <a href="https://www.darkreading.com/ics-ot-security/fuel-tank-monitoring-systems-vulnerable-disruption" target="_blank">Read more</a></p>
